H0.text: Loosely translated, Aleph Beth Gimel Daleth are the first four letters of what alphabet. Phoenician Alphabet

H1.text: Loosely translated, Aleph Beth Gimel Daleth are the first four letters of what alphabet. Aramaic Alphabet

H2.text: Loosely translated, Aleph Beth Gimel Daleth are the first four letters of what alphabet. Syriac Alphabet

H3.text: Loosely translated, Aleph Beth Gimel Daleth are the first four letters of what alphabet. עברית

A4.text: The Hebrew alphabet (Hebrew: אָלֶף־בֵּית עִבְרִי) is known as Alefbet ivri.

A5.text: The Hebrew script is an offshoot of the Imperial Aramaic alphabet, which itself derives from the Phoenician alphabet.
